 5. The kvm_run structure
@@ -8735,6 +8815,20 @@ This capability indicate to the userspace whether a PFNMAP memory region
 can be safely mapped as cacheable. This relies on the presence of
 force write back (FWB) feature support on the hardware.
 
+7.44 KVM_CAP_ARM_STAGE2_EXEC_GUARD
+----------------------------------
+
+:Architectures: arm64
+:Target: VM
+:Parameters: None; all ``args[]`` entries must be zero
+:Returns: 0 on success, -EINVAL if vCPUs already exist or an argument is nonzero
+
+This capability provides page-granular stage-2 execute mediation.  All guest
+pages start writable/execute-never.  A page becomes executable/read-only only
+after a pre-execute userspace exit and explicit approval; the first later
+write revokes execute and exits before modifying the page.  See
+``KVM_ARM_STAGE2_EXEC_GUARD``.
+
 8. Other capabilities.
